memberOrga:
EBMT members are centres that perform bone marrow transplantation. Physicians, nurses, scientists, data managers and quality managers working in those centres and listed as team members are considered members. &#xd;
&#xd;
Furthermore, our centre members can be divided into two categories: full members, or associate members. Our full members generously commit to submitting data on all patients treated in their centres on an annual basis, and enjoy the benefits of voting rights and eligibility for JACIE accreditation.&#xd;
&#xd;
Provisional centres are new members which are pending approval at the General Assembly Meeting during the EBMT Annual Meeting.&#xd;
&#xd;
EBMT also has individual members. &#xd;
&#xd;
Corporate membership is available to pharmaceutical and other companies in the field of blood cancers. See https://www.ebmt.org/ebmt/sponsors for the current list.&#xd;
&#xd;
Full details on membership can be found at https://www.ebmt.org/who-we-are/members
